Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Filed,  signed Deferred Prosecution Agreement(DPA).  The Court reviewed the DPA with the defendant.
The defendant was advised of her constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights received and filed.
The parties stipulate to the criminal complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry of Judgment of Conviction for a period of SIX months.
The Court approved the DPA and found it to be in the best interest of the parties and the general public.
Case adjourned to 5-31-2016 at 1:30PM. for review hearing in Branch 33. 
NOTE: Atty Renden stated that he has other matters for review on that date.

Defendant Amelia A Cuesta in court with attorney Gregory Allan Renden.  Randy P. Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Upon motion of the state, case is amended to 1 count of THEFT, a class A misdemeanor, 943.20(1)(a) & (3)(a).  Review hearing scheduled for May 31, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Amelia A Cuesta in court.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for Chad Wozniak for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant had been scheduled for court on 2-22-2016 for DPA hearing.  Atty Renden had appeared on that date.  Defendant was not present and the court issued a Bench Warrant.
Later that day, Atty Renden appeared and stated that the defendant had left a message for him that she was ill with the flu and could not appear.  Clerk advised Atty Renden that he and defendant are to appear on 2-23-2016 at 8:15am.
Clerk was contacted by the Clerk's office that the defendant was at the window in Room 117 Safety Building at 3pm on 2-22-2016 and she was being sent to Room 221.  Runner picked up file from courtroom.
Clerk was then contacted by Room 221 that felony warrants cannot be returned in that courtroom.  Defendant was advised to appear at 8:15 on 2-23-2016.
The court will withdraw the bench warrant(BW in file) and reinstate any bail.  Case is set for DPAH on 3-2-2016 at 8:15am.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for March 2, 2016 at 08:15 am.

COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE JUDGE ON RETURN OF THE BENCH WARRANT.
Any bail to be held for recompense.
